Package ru.ifmo.rain.zhelenskiy.implementor

Class Implementor

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.ifmo.rain.zhelenskiy.implementor.Implementor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Impler, JarImpler
    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements Impler, JarImpler
    This class implements interfaces and classes given by user. It has:
    • Method implement(Class, Path) that implements the given class and saves .java-file
    • Method implementJar(Class, Path) that implements the given class and creates runnable .jar-file.
    • Static method main(String[]) that gives the command line interface for using implement(Class, Path) and implementJar(Class, Path).
    See Also:
    Impler, JarImpler

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided Class. Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added.
        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        jarFile - target .jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation can not be generated.

      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
        Provides an interface for command line access to implement(Class, Path) and implementJar(Class, Path). Expected combinations of arguments:
        • 2 arguments to call implement(Class, Path) method (Class name and directory to save).
        • 3 arguments to call implementJar(Class, Path) method (Class name and target file to save). The first one must be --jar or -jar
        Parameters:
        args - command line arguments

      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class classes name should be same as classes name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java
        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation can not be generated.
